### Use with the "REST Client" extension in VS Code.
### The server must be running: npm run dev
### Reset data anytime with: npm run seed

@base = http://localhost:3000/api

### ---------- S6.1 — List products (10 pts) ----------

### All products (expect 5 products)
GET {{base}}/products

### Search filter (expect 1 product: "Jasmine Rice 5kg")
GET {{base}}/products?search=rice

### ---------- S6.2 — Customer with orders (10 pts) ----------

### Customer 2 with orders (expect Chan Mealea with 2 orders)
GET {{base}}/customers/2

### Unknown customer (expect 404)
GET {{base}}/customers/999

### ---------- S6.3 — Sales report, raw SQL (15 pts) ----------

### Expect on fresh seed (CANCELLED orders not counted):
### Instant Noodles Box = 15 sold / $15,
### Jasmine Rice 5kg = 2 / $16, Cooking Oil 1L = 1 / $4,
### Coca-Cola 6-Pack = 0 / $0 (its only order is CANCELLED),
### Palm Sugar 1kg = 0 / $0
GET {{base}}/reports/product-sales

### ---------- S7.1 — Place an order (25 pts) ----------

### Happy path (expect 201, status PENDING, totalPrice 2 x $6 = $12,
### then GET /products shows product 3 stock 30 -> 28)
POST {{base}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{ "customerId": 3, "productId": 3, "quantity": 2 }

### Quantity zero (expect 400)
POST {{base}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{ "customerId": 1, "productId": 1, "quantity": 0 }

### Not enough stock: product 5 has 0 (expect 409)
POST {{base}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{ "customerId": 1, "productId": 5, "quantity": 1 }

### Unknown customer (expect 404)
POST {{base}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{ "customerId": 999, "productId": 1, "quantity": 1 }

### Unknown product (expect 404)
POST {{base}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{ "customerId": 1, "productId": 999, "quantity": 1 }

### ---------- S7.2 — Cancel an order (10 pts) ----------

### Happy path: order 2 is PENDING, quantity 5 (expect 200,
### status CANCELLED, then GET /products shows product 1 stock 50 -> 55)
PUT {{base}}/orders/2/cancel

### Cancel the same order again (expect 409)
PUT {{base}}/orders/2/cancel

### Order 1 is PAID — cannot cancel (expect 409)
PUT {{base}}/orders/1/cancel

### Unknown order (expect 404)
PUT {{base}}/orders/999/cancel
